spans.text: for which Description's all too faint , And equal Misery alone
Sorrows for which Description's all too faint , And equal Misery alone
Sorrows for which Description's all too faint , And equal Misery alone
My hapless Flame nor Time nor Absence
constant to the Vows which made me yours
Which thy Ardelia does not equal feel
bids me from the dangerous Charmer fly
Let its fond Heart thy once-loved Chains resign , Complete thy Cure , and OH assist in mine
Complete thy Cure , and OH assist in mine
its fond Heart thy once-loved Chains resign ,
once more , Moneses , and renew Those tender Vows
those melting Eyes , Where Love a thousand nameless Charms
all his Empire in my Soul
The whispering Winds repeat the charming Sound
My own in streaming Tears to yours replies
thee that her Torments equal thine
Or why , OH why is it
my Reason and my Passion sway
all its sacred Precepts I pursue , Lost for a while
all its sacred Precepts I pursue , Lost for a while
the active Mind Still springs to thee
some happy Chance to us unknown , Without a Crime
To suffering Martyrs thus such Hopes
of promised Joys and future Heaven
of promised Joys and future Heaven
